This paper proposes a deep learning approach to semantic segmentation using a novel definition of contour evolution called Recurrent Level Set (RLS) and extends it to Contextual RLS (CRLS) for semantic segmentation in the wild. The paper focuses on computer vision and machine learning techniques, specifically deep learning and segmentation, which are typically covered in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of energy minimization and optimization techniques, which are relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the use of Gated Recurrent Units (GRUs) in the proposed method suggests a connection to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the experimental results involve medical imaging, which is relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
